"The second is physiological: small children especially would rather eat less than consume unfamiliar food. This rejection is stronger still in psychologically traumatized children suffering from anorexia due to illness and malnutrition. Chapter V indicated that, in most cultures whose food is supplied by agriculture rather than livestock, cereals and legumes are often combined. This greatly facilitates food aid, because both are dried and stored, and their nutrients are thus preserved in their most concentrated form."